GAMSAT Prep - Getting Ready for the Exam



The GAMSAT is regarded as one of the most difficult exams because it requires students to use various skills. GAMSAT prep includes enhancing your scientific knowledge, intellectual flexibility and an understanding of diagrammatic and textual information. You're also necessary to absorb this information with ease. To pass through the exam, you also need to be in a position to express yourself emotively and cogently. If you're thinking about joining medical school, this is a very important qualification to have. There are three main parts of the test. The first section includes reasoning in Social Sciences and Humanities. In this section, you will find 75 questions with multiple choices and you are expected to respond to them within 100 minutes. The second section of the exam is written communication and includes two essays that you are expected to finish in An hour. The 3rd section tests your reasoning within the biological and physical sciences and it has 110 questions which are supposed to be answered within 170 minutes.

